title.narrative: UNIVERSAL IMMUNIZATION

description.narrative: Universal immunization for immunizations, Deworming and VAS by 2016., which contributes to Adolescent Health And Nutrition, Child Health, Immunization, Polio Eradication. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2016, women and children in the most vulnerable districts have access to quality maternal and child health services, including nutrition, Prevention of Mother to Child Transmission of HIV (PMTCT) and Water, Sanitation, and Hygiene (WASH), and especially during emergencies.

title.narrative: Universal immunization for immunizations, Deworming and VAS by 2016.

description.narrative: UNICEF supported the country to switch to Bivalent Oral Polio Vaccine which reached 73,060 (90%) of children by December 2016, conduct the Measles- Rubella vaccination campaign which reached 794,223 (99%)children, and ensure routine immunization services reaching 96% of children with the 3rd dose of Pentavalent. | Status:Met | As-of Date:27/01/2017
